Jun 20 2009 	the checkout gotcha	The Jumeirah Carlton Tower is a deluxe hotel, not too large, in an excellent location with first class service. The health club is first rate, the swimming pool is large and there is even a room to hit golf balls and take a lesson. Amenities like these come with a price and everybody knows that London hotels are not inexpensive; however, I wasn't prepared for what awaited me at checkout.When I looked at my bill I discovered that the hotel had charged over 5 G.B. pounds (that's $8.20) a minute for a local phone call. In 5 days we made 5 calls that lasted a total of 18 minutes. The charge for the 5 calls was 99 pounds or $162 U.S. dollars.Besides the local calls I made, they had also a charge for long distance calls even though the calls were not completed-- no one answered the phone. I was so stunned by the audacity of the charge that I meekly paid the bill, still I can't believe that this is anything more than a giant rip-off. I may be mistaken; perhaps all London hotels treat their guests the same way. I hope not. My advice to travelers to the U.K. is to buy their own phone as soon as they arrive--one outside call at the Carlton Tower will pay for the phone.	
