Oct 19 2006 	Lovely stay great location	I was a little worried about this hotel as some of the reviews are not that complimentary and some of the 'candid' photos did not look too appealing. But I had no reason to be concerned.We stayed at the hotel for just one night. We were greeted with warm smiles, polite service and a quick/efficient check-in.The room was functional. It had everything you could want: LCD TV, Bose Wavemachine, fully stocked minibar...The bed was lovely and soft and the linen smelt fresh, by that I mean bed linen always appears fresh... this bed linen really smelt fresh.The bathroom was a work of art with the one piece full length glass shelf and sink. The bath also had a 'monsoon' effect showerhead and (nearly) everything worked and was clean.There was a turndown service and the maid not only turns the bed down but also leaves some lovely mini muffins in bags by the side of the bed together with two bottles of water and glasses ready for the night. In addition the curtains are drawn and the Bose is switched on with a cd playing peaceful, soothing music at a low volume. Trust me it is very pleasant to enter the room after a night out.We had a 10th floor room with a view out on to the main road. But the view was lovely and there is even a balcony to step out onto so you can watch Harrods light up in the early evening.Harrods and Harvey Nicks are five minutes away! As is the nearest tube.The fittings are all good quality, all electrical outlets/switches being chrome plated. You also get a complimentary guide to the area and even the pens feel as though they are good quality items.On the Sunday we had a paper delivered and it arrives in a bag with 'Good Morning' on the front and is hung from the door handle, not thrown on the floor!Every member of staff I met smiled, was friendly and helpful.The gym is great too. I very rarely use hotel gyms but the Carlton Tower has sensational views towards Battersea from the 9th floor. You can even join in with some aerobics etc.All in all, I loved my stay there and would have posted some better pictures, only I carelessly lost my camera somewhere in Knightsbridge.On the negative side. The handle on the outside of the balcony patio door had been broken off, so don't get hut out! The bath had a minor problem with the mechanism that empties the bath, but that would be easily repaired. And I caution you to be careful before ordering food, it is quite expensive, but the atmosphere is great.	
Apr 24 2006	Thanks to Sirius	Thanks to the Jumeirah loyalty scheme (Sirius) we managed a free night at the Carlton Tower! The location is very good, a stones throw from Harvey Nicks and Harrods. On allocation we were given the option of a non smoking twin or smoking double. We opted for the latter and found no issues with smell etc.Even though the room was 'standard' it was of a generous size, very clean and good quality, with lots of nice extras - Bose Cd player, 37 lcd tv, fruit platter, bottled water, welcome note etc. The bathroom was on the small side, but perfectly formed!All the staff I dealt with from the check in, doorman, garage attendant were helpful and polite.On the Sunday we visited the gym and pool, both of which were very good - but not outstanding.Note that parking at the hotel is £4.50 an hour or £45 overnight, the NCP close by is similar. Luckliy the local residents parking finished between 6:30 pm Sat. and 13:30 Sun. and there was no lack of space so we benefitted from that! (My BMW looked out of place amongst the Aston's and Bentley's in the garage anyway).One down side was the lift situation. Out of 3 lifts, 1 was out of order, and 1 being refurbished. So this led to small delays in getting the lift. By the reaction of some people you'd have thought they'd been asked to work for a living.Also the bar area always seemed busy with people having afternoon tea, we didn't find anywhere else for a early evening G&amp;T.In all a great night away, in yet another great Jumeirah property - thank you Jumeirah.	
