Mar 9 2006	My favourite London hotel	Have now stayed at the Carlton Tower about 20 times over the past 2 years. Service always fantastic and discrete staff respond to any needs of their customers. They welcome you back, give you decent rooms and only once have I had a problem with my bill at check out - quite unusual.The Rib Room is great for both dinner and for breakfast, but perhaps is a little stuffy for every evening so we usually go out as well.The bar is a bit small, but has a nice cosy feel about it providing you can get a table and/or seat. The pianist and singer and the friendly bar staff just seem to be there at the right time, without pressing you for drinks or ignoring you.The car is always cared for properly and cleaned immaculately for our departure and we never seem to have any minor irritating problems at this hotel (although recently the lifts have been refurbished and there is a longer wait than normal whilst the repairs are being carried out.I know its now a Jumeraih hotel, but the staff don't seem to have changed greatly, in fact many of the staff seem to have been there for a long time.It's a good hotel, really quiet, and in a great location.	
Jan 13 2006 	Losing it's appeal	Since Juneriah have taken over I've seen this hotel start to lose it's sparkle. Gone are the attentive lobby staff, only attend to you know if you're someone special. Gone are the Bvlgari bathroom products which was the biggest pull for me of this hotel, now replaced with tiny White products. Gone are hte bowls of fruits and roasted nuts. Air con seems to be hit and miss now, they used to have such a good system. The place is full of middle eastern clientele, it was quite heavily that way skewed before but the lobby area is now no longer a wonderfully relaxing destination at the beginning or end of the evening, it's too smoky and full of young men constantly playing with their mobile phones. The beds, size of rooms and Gym are still great but the proce you pay is harder to swallow for me now Jumeriah have attached their tag	
